<br>
When servers came up we all logged in (14 toons total) average /raid lvl 58 and sat a little east of the stairs.<br>
<br>
We kept buffed for the 6 hours we waited and about 6.5 hour he popped.   I pulled him about 40 yards to our party and took him down.<br>
<br>
We used three clerics and two druids with as fast heals as possible.  We learned from Wushi that fear/stun on heals SUCKS.  So anyways, just did little heals on me.  I lost agro once when I got stunned but regained it pretty quickly after stun /fear whore off.<br>
<br>
We never got a slow off on him, I dont even think the shaman was awake on pull )))  He hit max 500 but with as many healers/AA points there heals are 2-3seocnds 500-1600 heals so was pretty adequate.<br>
<br>
We have 4 epic rogues/Defenders Lightblades/LSoEE equiped.  Me and an epic mage.   They put adequate dmg out, no deaths.  Ill tell you I hated that camp, got so boring pulling tainted gorillas.  All the druids laughed (there all epiced) on how long they spent camping the tainted.<br>
<br>
Well, only suggestions I have is to get your guild in zone after a patch and sit and wait.  We had about 4 other guilds pop in but since they saw 10-14 people in a single guild they asked if Wushi was camped, we replied yes, and they left without a arguement. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mrkorb>MrKorb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/12/03 5:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://users.easystreet.com/korb/images/korb-annaart-glasses.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Down with Sev !!</span><hr size=1> I finally got my Sev last weekend after Inny crashed.  I had a lvl 42 ranger already camped there in the NW corner where nothing paths through.  Since I knew I was likely in for a long wait, I went off and watched some of those Star Trek: TNG DVDs that had been piling up.  After each episode, I came back to the computer, and hit the track key.  Now whenever I think of Sev, I'm going to associate him with the Scotty trapped in the transporter episode of TNG, lol.<br>
<br>
Anyways, my point is that camping a spawn like Sev is going to be annoying, long, and tedious if all you do is sit there in front of your computer for hours/days on end.  Find something else to do, and come back to the computer every 30 minutes and check for him.  Given how low the traffic in EJ is and how the warrior epic is percieved as a &quot;crappy weapon,&quot; I'd say if you find him up, he's yours.<br>
<br>
